	<article class="comment-item" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/UserComments">
		<p class="comment-author" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/bf3c6b145f9ab100a7691f3bde355cf0?s=48&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/bf3c6b145f9ab100a7691f3bde355cf0?s=96&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' itemprop="image" />			<cite class="fn">Juan Luis Varona</cite>		</p>
		<p class="comment-meta"> 
			<time class="comment-published" datetime="2012-08-30T02:14:29+02:00" title="Thursday, August 30, 2012, 2:14 am" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="https://texblog.org/2012/08/29/changing-the-font-size-in-latex/#comment-6132">30. August 2012 at 2:14</a></time>
					</p>
		<div class="comment-content">
			<p>The line height is assigned at the end of the paragraph.</p>
<p>So perhaps the solution for your doubt is to use</p>
<pre class="brush: latex; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">{\tiny Foo foo foo ... foo \par}</pre>
<p>or</p>
<pre class="brush: latex; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">{\Huge Foo foo foo ... foo \par}</pre>
		</div><!-- .comment-content -->
		<div class="reply">
			<a itemprop="replyToUrl"rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/08/29/changing-the-font-size-in-latex/?replytocom=6132#respond' data-commentid="6132" data-postid="1730" data-belowelement="comment-6132" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Juan Luis Varona'>Reply</a>		</div>
			
