<li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="comment-6140">
	<article class="comment-item" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/UserComments">
		<p class="comment-author" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/45435628abb56dd1acc9ac2ef104a2b1?s=48&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/45435628abb56dd1acc9ac2ef104a2b1?s=96&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' itemprop="image" />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://texblog.org' rel='external nofollow' class='url fn n' itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">tom</span></a></cite>		</p>
		<p class="comment-meta"> 
			<time class="comment-published" datetime="2013-01-22T04:08:40+02:00" title="Tuesday, January 22, 2013, 4:08 am" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="https://texblog.org/2012/08/29/changing-the-font-size-in-latex/#comment-6140">22. January 2013 at 4:08</a></time>
					</p>
		<div class="comment-content">
			<p>Hi Smufos,</p>
<p>Thanks for your question! The command <code>\par</code> ends the paragraph, that&#8217;s for sure. Now why <code>\par</code> does the trick, I&#8217;m not entirely sure. Apparently, TeX reads the whole paragraph first for optimal space adjustment between words. And manually ending the paragraph seems to also adjust <code>\baselineskip</code> when the font size is changed, whereas standard paragraph ending (blank line) does not. &#8220;The TeXbook&#8221; by Donald E. Knuth would be the right place to look for an answer :-).</p>
<p>Cheers, Tom.</p>
		</div><!-- .comment-content -->
