<li class="comment byuser comment-author-tom bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 role-administrator" id="comment-44286">
	<article class="comment-item" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/UserComments">
		<p class="comment-author" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/45435628abb56dd1acc9ac2ef104a2b1?s=48&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/45435628abb56dd1acc9ac2ef104a2b1?s=96&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' itemprop="image" />			<cite class="fn">tom</cite>		</p>
		<p class="comment-meta"> 
			<time class="comment-published" datetime="2017-05-23T22:41:12+02:00" title="Tuesday, May 23, 2017, 10:41 pm" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="https://texblog.org/2012/08/29/changing-the-font-size-in-latex/#comment-44286">23. May 2017 at 22:41</a></time>
					</p>
		<div class="comment-content">
			<p>Hi Zainab,</p>
<p>This should not happen. You can set the normal font size globally as an optional argument to documentclass.</p>
<pre class="brush: latex; title: ; notranslate" title="">\documentclass[12pt]{report}</pre>
<p>Whenever you use a macro to modify the font size locally, make sure you properly close it.</p>
<pre class="brush: latex; title: ; notranslate" title="">\begin{small}...\end{small}
% or
{\small ...}</pre>
		</div><!-- .comment-content -->
		<div class="reply">
			<a itemprop="replyToUrl"rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/08/29/changing-the-font-size-in-latex/?replytocom=44286#respond' data-commentid="44286" data-postid="1730" data-belowelement="comment-44286" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to tom'>Reply</a>		</div>
			
