<li class="comment byuser comment-author-tom bypostauthor even depth-2 role-administrator" id="comment-50959">
	<article class="comment-item" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/UserComments">
		<p class="comment-author" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/45435628abb56dd1acc9ac2ef104a2b1?s=48&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/45435628abb56dd1acc9ac2ef104a2b1?s=96&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' itemprop="image" />			<cite class="fn"><a href='https://texblog.org' rel='external nofollow' class='url fn n' itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">tom</span></a></cite>		</p>
		<p class="comment-meta"> 
			<time class="comment-published" datetime="2019-05-28T21:25:44+02:00" title="Tuesday, May 28, 2019, 9:25 pm" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="https://texblog.org/2012/08/29/changing-the-font-size-in-latex/#comment-50959">28. May 2019 at 21:25</a></time>
					</p>
		<div class="comment-content">
			<p>Hi Praveen,</p>
<p><code>13pt</code> is not an option. You could use the class defined in the <a href="https://ctan.org/pkg/extsizes?lang=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">extsizes package</a> to get a 14pt font size.</p>
<pre class="brush: latex; title: ; notranslate" title="">\documentclass[14pt]{extreport}</pre>
<p>HTH, Tom</p>
		</div><!-- .comment-content -->
